<F P=106> [From the "National Hookup" program] </F>
  [Text] Premier Li Peng presided over a ceremony at the 
Central Hall of the Great Hall of the People this evening in 
honor of Japanese Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa, who is on an 
official visit to China. 
  Qian Qichen, vice premier and foreign minister, and others 
were present at the welcoming ceremony. 
  After the ceremony, Premier Li Peng and Prime Minister 
Morihiro Hosokawa held a friendly conversation. Following that, 
Li Peng hosted a banquet in honor of Prime Minister Hosokawa and 
Mrs. Hosokawa. 
  Prime Minister Hosokawa and his entourage arrived in Beijing 
around noon today. Chen Jinhua, minister in charge of the State 
Planning Commission and chairman of the Chinese Reception 
Committee; Xu Dunxin, Chinese ambassador to Japan; Vice Foreign 
Minister Tang Jiaxuan; and Japanese Ambassador to China 
Michihiko Kunihiro greeted him at the airport. 

